---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Fin Sanctuary • Diamond Dave"
  description="Learn about Diamond Dave, the aquarium hobbyist and 3D-print designer behind Fin Sanctuary and its beginner-friendly tank resources."
  ogImage="/images/og/about.svg"
>
  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-primary/10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(1,133,174,0.08),rgba(243,239,238,0.55))] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(13,175,188,0.14),rgba(2,6,23,0.95))]">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-8 px-6 py-10 md:py-12 xl:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_24rem] xl:items-end">
        <div>
          <div class="text-[0.72rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-primary/75">Profile</div>
          <h1 class="mt-5 font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Diamond Dave</h1>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
            Aquarium hobbyist, guide builder, and 3D-print accessory designer based in Norman, Oklahoma. Fin Sanctuary is built around the kind of practical tank advice I wish more beginners had at the start: realistic stocking, cleaner maintenance habits, and setups that actually fit the space and schedule people live with. I care most about helping people avoid expensive mistakes, unnecessary fish loss, and the kind of confusing advice that makes the hobby feel harder than it needs to be.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
            If you want to reach me directly, email <a href="mailto:drodge00@finsanctuary.com" class="font-semibold text-primary underline decoration-primary/35 underline-offset-4" data-track-click="email_click" data-track-location="about-profile" data-track-label="drodge00@finsanctuary.com" data-track-category="contact" data-track-destination="mailto:drodge00@finsanctuary.com">drodge00@finsanctuary.com</a>. You can also contact me through the <a href="/contact" class="font-semibold text-primary underline decoration-primary/35 underline-offset-4" data-track-click="cta_click" data-track-location="about-profile" data-track-label="Contact Page" data-track-category="contact" data-track-destination="/contact">contact page</a>, which also lists the other Fin Sanctuary email addresses by purpose.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-8 text-[0.72rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-primary/75">About the Site</div>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
            Fin Sanctuary is meant to help people avoid the expensive mistakes that happen when a tank is planned around impulse instead of fit.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 shadow-[0_28px_90px_-55px_rgba(1,133,174,0.45)] backdrop-blur dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900/82">
          <img
            src="/images/about/finsanctuary-about-me.png"
            alt="Diamond Dave smiling beside a planted aquarium"
            class="h-[26rem] w-full object-cover object-center"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-10">
      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.1fr)_minmax(0,0.9fr)]">
        <article class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white px-7 py-8 shadow-[0_24px_80px_-55px_rgba(1,133,174,0.42)] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900 md:px-9">
          <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Why this site exists</h2>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <p>Too many aquarium sites either stay too shallow to be useful or jump straight into advanced hobby jargon. This project is aimed at the middle: practical guidance for people setting up an aquarium in a living room, bedroom, kitchen, waiting area, or small office.</p>
            <p>The goal is not to impress advanced hobbyists with complexity. The goal is to help normal people make good decisions about tank size, fish choice, maintenance, filtration, accessories, and long-term care.</p>
            <p>The 3D-printed products on this site are meant to support that same idea. They should solve real tank problems cleanly, not just add novelty.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="space-y-6">
          <section class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white p-6 dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900">
            <div class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary/75">Audience</div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Home and small-office aquarium owners in the USA who want a tank that looks good, stays healthy, and is realistic to maintain.</p>
          </section>
          <section class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white p-6 dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900">
            <div class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary/75">What to expect</div>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
              <li>Wizard-based recommendations</li>
              <li>Long-form aquarium guides</li>
              <li>3D-printed accessory sales</li>
              <li>Future newsletter and gallery expansion</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
